23:46.508 --> 23:48.552
I want to see what they're
going to do to your blades.

23:48.552 --> 23:51.388
I'm not too concerned what your
blades do to them.

23:51.388 --> 23:53.432
Nicholas, you're up first.
How are you feeling?

23:53.432 --> 23:55.309
- A little nervous.
- We're gonna do it anyway, so.

23:55.309 --> 23:57.519
- I know, I know.
- Okay, let's do it.

23:57.519 --> 23:59.688
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:59.688 --> 24:01.357
<i>- I'm feeling as nervous</i>
<i>as I felt</i>

24:01.357 --> 24:03.067
<i>going into this competition,</i>

24:03.067 --> 24:05.235
<i>but I'm fairly confident</i>
<i>in the edge.</i>

24:05.235 --> 24:07.488
<i>I'm very confident</i>
<i>in the hammer.</i>

24:07.488 --> 24:10.532
<i>If those pry teeth hold up.</i>
<i>I might just stand a chance.</i>

24:10.532 --> 24:17.456
♪ ♪

24:29.468 --> 24:33.263
- [grunts]

24:33.263 --> 24:35.599
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:35.599 --> 24:38.602
- All right, Nicholas,
we've got a couple issues here.

24:38.602 --> 24:42.356
During the pry, it popped off
one of your teeth here,

24:42.356 --> 24:44.775
and it actually, instead of
pulling the nail out further,

24:44.775 --> 24:48.404
it actually buried the head
further into the wood block.

24:48.404 --> 24:51.031
Now, coming over
to the hammer strike,

24:51.031 --> 24:52.616
having this down here,

24:52.616 --> 24:54.493
it's like taking
a hammer at home,

24:54.493 --> 24:56.286
cutting the handle off
and just trying to use that.

24:56.286 --> 24:58.914
That's a big design flaw
right there.

24:58.914 --> 25:02.584
On the plus side, your blade
edge held up pretty well.

25:02.584 --> 25:04.461
Mark, how are you feeling
after seeing that?

25:04.461 --> 25:07.297
- Tear it up.
- Oh, don't tell me that.

25:07.297 --> 25:09.633
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:09.633 --> 25:12.344
<i>- I'm feeling</i>
<i>excited and nervous.</i>

25:12.344 --> 25:16.056
I hope my blade doesn't
explode, but, either way,

25:16.056 --> 25:18.434
<i>I'm in a good mood.</i>

25:18.434 --> 25:25.441
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:42.332 --> 25:44.543
- Mark, overall, I like this.

25:44.543 --> 25:46.587
The pry tines
are a little bit tight.

25:46.587 --> 25:49.173
I had to actually wedge it
in there to get that nail out.

25:49.173 --> 25:51.300
The problem I have
is the hammerhead.

25:51.300 --> 25:54.428
It's not that much wider
than the nail heads itself,

25:54.428 --> 25:57.890
so it's really hard getting
an accurate strike on there.

25:57.890 --> 26:00.559
On your edge, it actually
held up pretty well.

26:00.559 --> 26:04.021
You've got little
wrinkles there, but, overall,

26:04.021 --> 26:06.231
everything stayed tight.
Good job,

26:06.231 --> 26:07.816
- Cool. Thank you.

26:07.816 --> 26:09.526
- So, Garrin,
how are you feeling?

26:09.526 --> 26:11.278
- I'm feeling a little bit

26:11.278 --> 26:13.072
more nervous than I was before.

26:13.072 --> 26:15.574
- Okay, well, let's see
what happens here.

26:15.574 --> 26:17.659
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:17.659 --> 26:19.953
<i>- When I saw Nicholas'</i>
<i>fork break, I thought,</i>

26:19.953 --> 26:22.623
"Oh, God, this can't
