26:22.623 --> 26:24.500
<i>I've got the same steel.</i>

26:24.500 --> 26:26.710
<i>I've got the same design,</i>

26:26.710 --> 26:29.476
so I'm worried about the same
exact thing happening for me.

26:49.650 --> 26:52.569
- All right, Garrin. Obviously,
we've got a problem here.

26:52.569 --> 26:55.739
It was such a clean break,
what I'm thinking

26:55.739 --> 26:58.033
is you probably had some kind
of a microfracture in the edge

26:58.033 --> 26:59.868
that we couldn't even see.

26:59.868 --> 27:01.620
Trying to lever it up,

27:01.620 --> 27:03.497
the teeth were just
burying in the wood.

27:03.497 --> 27:06.500
So when I tried to jam in
and lever it up the other way.

27:06.500 --> 27:09.253
Bang. That's when
we blew apart.

27:09.253 --> 27:11.421
- Nicholas, Garrin, both of you
had a problem

27:11.421 --> 27:13.423
in the strength test.

27:13.423 --> 27:15.676
Nicholas, your blade suffered
significant damage by

27:15.676 --> 27:17.845
<i>losing one of the teeth,</i>

27:17.845 --> 27:20.472
However, we were able to do
the chop test with your blade.

27:20.472 --> 27:22.933
Garrin, your blade
snapped in half.

27:22.933 --> 27:24.893
<i>That is catastrophic</i>
<i>blade damage,</i>

27:24.893 --> 27:26.645
and you can no longer
even continue

27:26.645 --> 27:28.313
with our strength test,

27:28.313 --> 27:30.816
and for that reason,
I have to ask you, Garrin,

27:30.816 --> 27:33.485
to please leave The Forge.

27:33.485 --> 27:35.112
- [bleep].

27:35.112 --> 27:37.197
I'm feeling pretty [bleep].

27:37.197 --> 27:39.157
<i>I agree with the decision</i>
<i>that the judges made,</i>

27:39.157 --> 27:43.287
but I really wanted to see
Doug do a cutting test.

27:43.287 --> 27:44.955
Knives are not crowbars.

27:44.955 --> 27:48.333
Tell your friends.

27:48.333 --> 27:51.128
- Mark, Nick, congratulations.

27:51.128 --> 27:52.254
You've made it
into the final round

27:52.254 --> 27:53.964
of this competition,

27:53.964 --> 27:55.632
which means that you're both
one step closer

27:55.632 --> 27:57.676
to the title
of "Forged in Fire" champion

27:57.676 --> 27:59.678
and that check for 10 grand.

27:59.678 --> 28:02.222
All you need to do now
is defeat the man next to you

28:02.222 --> 28:04.016
by going back
to your home forge

28:04.016 --> 28:06.518
and re-creating an iconic
weapon from history...

28:06.518 --> 28:09.855
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:09.855 --> 28:11.523
The Russian Pioneer Sword.

28:11.523 --> 28:14.568
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:14.568 --> 28:16.778
<i>The multipurpose</i>
<i>Russian Pioneer Sword</i>

28:16.778 --> 28:19.156
<i>was a key utility tool</i>
<i>for European troops</i>

28:19.156 --> 28:21.199
<i>in the 18th and 19th</i>
<i>centuries.</i>

28:21.199 --> 28:23.660
<i>Used extensively</i>
<i>during the Crimean war,</i>

28:23.660 --> 28:26.079
<i>it was carried by pioneers</i>
<i>assigned to build bridges</i>

28:26.079 --> 28:28.582
<i>and construct trenches</i>
<i>for the military.</i>

28:28.582 --> 28:30.918
<i>The blade contained</i>
<i>sharp, serrated saw teeth</i>

28:30.918 --> 28:33.003
<i>covering its spine</i>
<i>and was extremely effective</i>

28:33.003 --> 28:34.796
<i>for chopping down</i>
<i>trees and shrubs</i>

28:34.796 --> 28:37.341
<i>as the troops traveled</i>
<i>through rough terrain.</i>

28:37.341 --> 28:39.217
<i>While mainly used as a tool,</i>

28:39.217 --> 28:41.261
<i>this short, handy sidearm's</i>
<i>jagged edges</i>

28:41.261 --> 28:43.263
<i>could also be used</i>
<i>in self-defense</i>

28:43.263 --> 28:45.140
<i>and was capable of</i>
<i>ripping through both skin</i>

28:45.140 --> 28:47.017
<i>and bone of enemy forces,</i>

28:47.017 --> 28:51.229
<i>particularly in close combat.</i>

28:51.229 --> 28:52.773
The blades themselves must fall

28:52.773 --> 28:54.650
within the following
parameters:

28:54.650 --> 28:57.277
you must have a fuller
on each side of the blade.

28:57.277 --> 28:59.446
You must also have
a functional sawback

28:59.446 --> 29:02.157
and have a cast bronze
guard and handle

29:02.157 --> 29:04.993
with decorative file
work on the handle.

29:04.993 --> 29:07.079
<i>- The casting part of it</i>
<i>is the thing</i>

29:07.079 --> 29:09.539
that I'm least experienced at,

29:09.539 --> 29:11.959
<i>so hopefully, I don't</i>
<i>run into any pitfalls</i>

29:11.959 --> 29:13.835
<i>with the foundry work.</i>

29:13.835 --> 29:15.754
<i>It's gonna be tough.</i>

29:15.754 --> 29:17.047
- Bladesmiths, you will have
five days at your home forge

29:17.047 --> 29:18.882
to complete this challenge.

29:18.882 --> 29:20.634
At the end of five days,
you'll return and present

29:20.634 --> 29:22.803
your blades to a panel
of expert judges,

29:22.803 --> 29:25.389
and only after they've
thoroughly tested your weapons

29:25.389 --> 29:27.683
will they declare one of you
the "Forged in Fire" champion

29:27.683 --> 29:29.643
and give you that 10 grand.

29:29.643 --> 29:32.104
Good luck.
We'll see you in five days.

29:32.104 --> 29:34.064
- Good luck.
- Good luck.

29:34.064 --> 29:37.317
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:37.317 --> 29:40.153
<i>- It feels really excellent</i>
<i>to have made it this far.</i>

29:40.153 --> 29:43.073
We are making
a Russian Pioneer Sword.

29:43.073 --> 29:46.535
<i>The things that I want</i>
<i>to get accomplished today are,</i>

29:46.535 --> 29:49.371
cut out some mild steel
to build some casting frames

29:49.371 --> 29:52.582
that'll be the right side to
cast my brass handle and guard.

29:52.582 --> 29:54.876
<i>That's gonna be the hard part.</i>

29:54.876 --> 29:58.171
<i>I've also got some 1084 and 15</i>
<i>and 20 for the Damascus blade.</i>

29:58.171 --> 29:59.923
<i>I think there's</i>
<i>a low probability</i>

29:59.923 --> 30:01.967
<i>that Mark is gonna</i>
<i>screw something up,</i>

30:01.967 --> 30:05.345
so I feel like it's really
gonna come down to the details.

30:05.345 --> 30:07.180
This is probably
the largest billet

30:07.180 --> 30:09.349
of Damascus I've done
in this forge.

30:09.349 --> 30:11.935
<i>I definitely think that</i>
<i>I'm the underdog right now.</i>

30:11.935 --> 30:13.645
<i>I just barely scraped by</i>
<i>in the first two rounds</i>

30:13.645 --> 30:15.647
<i>by the skin of my teeth,</i>

30:15.647 --> 30:17.190
but I'm confident that
this week is gonna go well.

30:19.151 --> 30:22.112
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:22.112 --> 30:24.031
<i>- I'm nervous about a couple</i>
<i>of the aspects</i>

30:24.031 --> 30:26.158
of making this sword.

30:26.158 --> 30:29.578
<i>Casting is the thing</i>
<i>I feel like I'm weakest at.</i>

30:29.578 --> 30:32.664
<i>My goal for the first day</i>
<i>is to make a pattern</i>

30:32.664 --> 30:35.167
<i>so I can cast</i>
<i>the bronze handle.</i>

30:35.167 --> 30:37.836
I need to set a mold with sand

30:37.836 --> 30:41.173
<i>meld a crucible of</i>
<i>bronze, and cast it.</i>

30:41.173 --> 30:42.924
There's gonna be some
professional foundry people

30:42.924 --> 30:45.385
out there laughing
their asses off at this.

30:45.385 --> 30:47.345
Hopefully the bronze
filled all the cavities

30:47.345 --> 30:49.806
and we got a good
handle to work with,

30:49.806 --> 30:53.101
but whatever comes
we have to roll with it.

30:53.101 --> 30:54.686
[bleep].

30:54.686 --> 30:56.730
<i>It blew out on the mold.</i>

30:56.730 --> 30:58.690
<i>I wasted an hour and a half</i>

30:58.690 --> 31:00.776
<i>getting the metal up</i>
<i>to liquid temperature.</i>

31:00.776 --> 31:03.070
<i>I'm hoping that I'm not</i>
<i>still working on this</i>

31:03.070 --> 31:05.363
in the last three minutes
of the challenge.

31:05.363 --> 31:07.365
I guess we're gonna
do this tomorrow.

31:07.365 --> 31:09.201
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:09.201 --> 31:10.744
- Yesterday I finished
forking the blade.

31:10.744 --> 31:13.997
Today I need
to cast a bit of bronze.

31:13.997 --> 31:17.459
It's time to try out
these casting frames.

31:17.459 --> 31:19.294
I feel like I got
my ducks in a row.

31:19.294 --> 31:22.255
I'm starting out with metal.

31:22.255 --> 31:24.466
It looks really hot.

31:24.466 --> 31:26.760
All right, we have liquid
metal.

31:26.760 --> 31:29.638
This the most metal I've ever
tried to pour a mold from.

31:32.015 --> 31:33.809
Well, I kind of can't believe
it,

31:33.809 --> 31:35.811
but it actually looks like
it came out really well.

31:35.811 --> 31:38.188
I'm very pleased; I think that
looks pretty awesome.

31:38.188 --> 31:40.148
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:40.148 --> 31:44.069
- Yesterday the casting
was successful, so today,

31:44.069 --> 31:46.655
<i>I'm gonna forge out the blade</i>

31:46.655 --> 31:49.491
<i>I'm using a piece of 51/60</i>
<i>tool steel.</i>

31:49.491 --> 31:52.619
I'm gonna forge out a blade
that's gonna be stout enough

31:52.619 --> 31:54.871
<i>for whatever they're</i>
<i>gonna test it on.</i>

31:54.871 --> 31:56.540
By the end of the day,

31:56.540 --> 31:58.458
I'd like to have all
of the forging done,

31:58.458 --> 32:01.878
<i>so tomorrow we can focus</i>
<i>on the heat treat.</i>

32:01.878 --> 32:04.089
Looks very phallic.

32:04.089 --> 32:05.966
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:05.966 --> 32:09.845
- It is day 5,
and I feel pretty good.

32:09.845 --> 32:12.556
<i>Yesterday the quench</i>
<i>went pretty well.</i>

32:12.556 --> 32:13.557
<i>I have</i>
<i>a couple of little warps</i>

32:13.557 --> 32:15.267
<i>that I have to take out,</i>

32:15.267 --> 32:16.726
but I think I ought to be able
to tweak that

32:16.726 --> 32:18.520
without too much problem.

32:18.520 --> 32:20.188
<i>I'm gonna stick some wires</i>
<i>in the vise</i>

32:20.188 --> 32:21.815
<i>and see</i>
<i>if I can't true it up a bit.</i>

32:21.815 --> 32:23.775
If it can't survive this,

32:23.775 --> 32:24.776
then it doesn't have
